{% extends 'layouts/page.njk' %}

{% block content %}
  {{ appHeading({
    text: heading,
    caption: "GOV.UK Content Review"
  }) }}

  <div class="govuk-grid-row">
    <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
      <div class="govuk-body" data-testid="app-page-body">
        <p class="govuk-body-l">
          An AI-powered content review service designed to ensure your content meets GOV.UK standards and accessibility requirements.
        </p>
        
        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Purpose of this service</h2>
        <p>The AI Content Review service assists content designers and policy teams by:</p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>evaluating content for plain English and clarity</li>
          <li>assessing compliance with GOV.UK style guidelines</li>
          <li>identifying areas for improvement in readability and accessibility</li>
          <li>providing evidence-based recommendations for content enhancement</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Using this service</h2>
        <p>To submit content for review, enter or paste your text into the content field on the home page. The AI will analyse your content against established GOV.UK standards and provide comprehensive feedback.</p>
        
        <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">Content requirements</h3>
        <p>Content submitted for review must meet the following criteria:</p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>between <strong>10 and 100,000 characters</strong> in length</li>
          <li>plain text format (visual formatting elements such as bold text, headings, or hyperlinks will not be evaluated)</li>
          <li>written in English</li>
        </ul>
        
        <div class="govuk-inset-text">
          <p>For optimal results, we recommend submitting content in manageable sections (individual pages or distinct content blocks) rather than extensive documents.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Processing time</h2>
        <p>Reviews are typically completed within 30 seconds to 2 minutes. Processing time may vary depending on:</p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>content length and complexity</li>
          <li>current service demand</li>
          <li>analysis depth required</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p>The review history will automatically refresh upon completion. You may navigate away from the page during processing - your completed review will remain accessible in the review history.</p>

        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Error handling and retry mechanism</h2>
        <p>In the event of temporary service interruptions, the system will automatically retry your review request without requiring user intervention. This ensures reliable processing even during periods of high demand or brief service unavailability.</p>
        
        <p>Should a review fail after multiple automated retry attempts, an error notification will be displayed. In such cases, please resubmit your content for review.</p>

        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Review criteria and methodology</h2>
        <p>The AI evaluation framework assesses content against 5 key quality dimensions:</p>

        <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">1. Plain English</h3>
        <p>Assessment includes:</p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>use of clear, accessible language with minimal jargon</li>
          <li>average sentence length (target: 15-20 words)</li>
          <li>identification of GOV.UK discouraged terminology (such as "utilise", "facilitate", "going forward")</li>
          <li>opportunities to simplify complex vocabulary</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">2. Clarity and Structure</h3>
        <p>Evaluation criteria:</p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>logical organisation and flow of information</li>
          <li>scannability and readability metrics</li>
          <li>user-centred approach prioritising audience needs</li>
          <li>active voice preference over passive constructions</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">3. Accessibility</h3>
        <p>Analysis encompasses:</p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>language complexity and reading age suitability</li>
          <li>presence of unexplained technical terminology</li>
          <li>potential barriers for users with diverse abilities</li>
          <li>overall content inclusivity</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">4. GOV.UK Style Compliance</h3>
        <p>Verification includes:</p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>adherence to GOV.UK style guide conventions for language and tone</li>
          <li>correct formatting of numerals and time references (for example, "9am" rather than "nine o'clock")</li>
          <li>appropriate voice and tone for government communications</li>
          <li>elimination of corporate terminology and ambiguous phrases</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">5. Content Completeness</h3>
        <p>Quality assessment determines whether:</p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>all essential information is present and accurate</li>
          <li>instructions are clear, specific, and actionable</li>
          <li>content gaps or omissions exist</li>
          <li>content length is proportionate to the subject matter</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="govuk-inset-text">
          <p><strong>Important:</strong> The AI review analyses plain text content only. Visual formatting elements such as headings, lists, or hyperlinks are not evaluated. The focus is exclusively on language quality and content structure.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Review output</h2>
        <p>Upon completion, each review provides:</p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>a comprehensive summary with scores for each of the 5 assessment categories</li>
          <li>your original content with colour-coded annotations highlighting specific issues</li>
          <li>prioritised recommendations identifying the top 5 improvements with contextual examples and suggested revisions</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

{% endblock %}
